  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "OpenZeppelin has a wonderful, modular approach where many contracts build upon simpler ones.\r\n\r\nHowever, because of the semi-object-oriented way Solidity works, it is possible to, on purpose or by accident, modify behavior that one of the ancestor contracts provides.\r\n\r\nFor instance, I would expect any contracts that inherit from `Ownable`, to check if `transferOwnership` [indeed transfers ownership](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/zeppelin-solidity/blob/master/test/Ownable.js#L18).\r\n\r\nI believe these tests are important because they could prevent accidental alterations to behaviour specified by an ancestor contract that would otherwise probably go unnoticed until the Smart Contract is deployed and in use.",
